The restaurant, wine bar & pub are all top notch and well worth a visit although no breakfast was available during our visit.	In addition, we received $10 a day for breakfast at UVA, a wine bar next to the hotel.	Everything is within walking distance - including a grocery store, coffee shops, Robson Street, fancy restaurants, fast-food restaurants, etc.	Hotel is an old building, and not very easy to find - it is part of a wine bar and restaurant.	We enjoyed not having to walk more than a few blocks to restaurants, bars, and coffee shops.